vice</b> to/from the airport was launched. The service was discontinued in April 2017 without an announced date to be resumed. <a class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://belarusfeed.com/airport-train-cancelled/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">[23]</a>\n\nFor <i>car</i> from the airport, there are several options. The official airport transfer service <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://airport.by/en/tourism/transfer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">National Airport Minsk</a> has a good reputation with short number 7373. But the official airport transfer service has several important shortcomings: Chinese cars, non-English speaking drivers, low quality of service in general. If you looking for higher level of service you can use private transfer services like <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.autotransfer.by/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">Autotransfer</a> or <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.minskairporttransfer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">Minsk Airport Transfer</a>. It should cost about €25-30 and transfers can be ordered in advance using online booking form. Taxis are available at the airport although drivers generally will not speak English – have the name of your destination written in Belorussian or Russian and be prepared to pay in cash. There\'s also Uber in Minsk now. If you have a cell phone, this is probably the easiest and cheapest option – a ride into town can be as cheap as €10.", "Getting to the city", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "226-autosave-v1", "", "", "2017-09-13 11:22:08", "2017-09-13 08:22:08", "", "226", "http://ocsico.loc/%d0%b1%d0%b5%d0%b7-%d1%80%d1%83%d0%b1%d1%80%d0%b8%d0%ba%d0%b8/226-autosave-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
